Hello, 
 as stated in the title I'm seeing different behaviors while playing the same file.
I'm testing this on an old kind phone LG4 and on a new one S8+.

The problem is simple when I play the animation on the LG4 (very slow phone) it actually plays smoothly.
On the other device instead (S8+) I see the animation going like is bouncing back few frames and then moving forward. 

I don't think there is nothing strange with my animation because I also tried with the testing animations on github website. 
I tried to enable or disable hardware acceleration and nothing change.
Also the disk chace strategy is set to strong , same no changes.
I have no onUpdate listeners.
I only run 3 different animations at the same time.
I'm using it as popup menu button with 2 more options coming from the back of the main menu button.
After 600 milliseconds it should pause.
 (also there is another problem that the timing is never the same on the exact frame but I understand why and I kind solved that).

            Handler handler = new Handler();
            handler.postDelayed(()-> {
                    btn_t.pauseAnimation();
                    btn_minus.pauseAnimation();
                    btn_plus.pauseAnimation();
                    btn_plus.setClickable(true);
                    btn_minus.setClickable(true);
            }, 600);
            playTBtns();

Now Do you have any idea why is behaving like that ?
